The paper focuses on the collaboration between humans and autonomous agents in a skill transfer scenario, which involves reinforcement learning and communication. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category, which deals with the design, evaluation, and implementation of interactive computing systems for human use. The paper also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO), as it discusses the use of autonomous agents to teach complex skills to humans. Additionally, the paper may fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category, as it involves reinforcement learning, and the systems (human and robot) are acting as reinforcement learners. Finally, the paper may also belong to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category, as it discusses the development of a successful robot-human collaborative framework.
